==English==
[[Image:Gnocchi cooked.jpg|thumb|300px|right|Gnocchi in a tomato sauce.]]
===Etymology===
{{It.}} ''gnocchi'', plural of ''[[gnocco]]'', [[dumpling]]; literally meaning [[lump]], from a Germanic word for a [[knot]] (as in [[wood]])

===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): /ˈnjɒki/, /<tt>"njQki</tt>/
*(''US''): nyō'kē, /ˈnjoʊki/, /<tt>"njoUki</tt>/ ''or'' nyŏ'kē, /ˈnjɑki/, /<tt>"njAki</tt>/

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''gnocchi''' ''plural'' (''not used in the singular'')

#[[Italian]] [[pasta]]-like dumplings made of [[potato]] or [[semolina]].

